<TITLE> Law enforcers on maximum alert: Sahara </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Nov 16 (bdnews24.com)--The law-enforcing agencies have been put on maximum alert to pre-empt any untoward situation ahead of the announcement of the final verdict in Bangabandhu murder trial on Nov 19, the home minister says. Sahara Khatun said on Monday the government is not fearing violence but taking additional precautionary measures. Monitoring in the courts and important establishments has been strengthened. "The extra steps have been taken to assure people about their security which is a responsibility of the government," Sahara told reporters after a meeting with the heads of law-enforcing agencies at the Secretariat. The forces are ready to tackle any incident or conspiracy, she added. Replying to a question she said red alert has been announced through Interpol against the absconding convicts in the case. They will be brought back once traced, the minister said. Her deputy Shamsul Huq Tuku said intelligence agencies also are on alert around the country. Home secretary Abdus Sobhan Sikder, police chief Nur Mohammad and director general of RAB Hassan Mahmud Khandaker were also present in the meeting. bdn
